From e43ef329561b8d0d809d1ad283a7ee4fa473ed1f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Patrick Gill <patrickgill@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 17:46:46 +1000
Subject: [PATCH 01/13] Fix lwr/lwl unaligned load in PSX (lwr-before-lwl)
 order

PSX GCC emits unaligned 32-bit loads as lwr/lwl pairs where the
relative offset ordering can go either way:
  - lwl $dst, N+3($base) then lwr $dst, N($base)  [lwl-before-lwr]
  - lwr $dst, N($base)   then lwl $dst, N+3($base) [lwr-before-lwl]

The existing code handled lwl-before-lwr only via a signed delta check
that fails when the offsets are reversed relative to the expected endian
convention.

Add a `Lwr` marker class symmetric to `Lwl`: when handle_lwr finds no
matching Lwl in the register, it stores Lwr as a temporary marker.
handle_lwl then detects the marker (via get_raw to bypass the inputs
check) and emits UnalignedLoad.

Also handle the case where lwl-before-lwr appears with reversed offsets
(lwl at N+3, lwr at N in BE mode) by checking both delta signs in
handle_lwr.

Add end-to-end test for the lwr-before-lwl pattern.
